modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and generating JavaScript code from template strings, including variable substitution and conditional blocks. Operates on strings and abstract syntax trees specific to JavaScript syntax. Used to dynamically generate client-side scripts based on configuration files or user input.

Creates DOM nodes from an XML tree, using a specified document or the default one. Accepts an XML rewrite tree and returns a DOM node hierarchy. Useful for dynamically generating and inserting HTML elements in JavaScript environments.
